Business Brief -- Leslie Fay Cos.:
   Apparel Maker to Receive
   New Financing From Banks
The new three-year agreement replaces a package due to
expire next December. Leslie Fay also has an option to extend
the funding for a fourth year.
   The bank lenders include the Manufacturers Hanover unit of
Chemical Banking Corp.; Marine Midland Bank, N.A.; National
Westminster Bank U.S.A., and Bank of New York.
   "Interest rates are low, and if you are a good credit,
it's a good time to negotiate a banking agreement," said Paul
Polishan, Leslie Fay's chief financial officer. He noted that
both National Westminster and Bank of New York are new
lenders.